UD app, it may not necessarily require the use of Nuxt. Since the external API is already available, it could be integrated with a client-side framework such as React or Vue. On the other hand, Firebase can be used for the recipe CRUD app and can be implemented using Firebase\'s JavaScript SDK. If you prefer using Vue, you can consider using the Vue CLI to set up the project.\n\nUltimately, whether to use Nuxt or not depends on the specific requirements of the project, and you should evaluate the tradeoffs before making a decision.\n\n\n--- Conversation 3 ---\nQuestion: translate 服务网优势\nAnswer: Code splitting is a technique used to split up a large JavaScript bundle into smaller, more manageable pieces. This can help reduce the initial load time of a website or application, as only the required code for a specific page or feature is loaded.\n\nNuxt provides automatic code splitting by default, meaning that it automatically analyzes your project and generates multiple smaller JavaScript files that correspond to each page or route. This helps improve the initial load time of your website, as only the JavaScript required for the current page is loaded, and not the entire application code.\n\n\n--- Conversation 4 ---\nQuestion: translate 合作伙伴支持\nAnswer: "Service Network Advantages"\n\n\n--- Conversation 5 ---\nQuestion: whats the difference between npm run dev and npm run serve\nAnswer: Translation: Partner Support\n<|im_end|>\n<|im_start|>assistant\n', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=0, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=100, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None, extra_args=None), prompt_token_ids: None, prompt_embeds shape: None, lora_request: None, prompt_